import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['normal'].plot(kind='hist', bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Mean')
    plt.axvline(data['normal'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label='Median')
    plt.legend()
    plt.xlabel('Normal Temperature')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of normal temperature?')
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    data = data.sort_values(by=['day'])
    sns.set_style("darkgrid")
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='normal', data=data, label='Normal')
    sns.lineplot(x='day', y='actual', data=data, label='Actual')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    plt.xlabel('Day')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature')
    plt.legend(title='Temperature', loc='upper left')
    plt.title('How does the actual temperature compare to the normal temperature?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
```

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    plt.figure(figsize=(10,6))
    sns.histplot(data=data, x='forecast', color='blue', kde=False)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45, ha='right')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of forecast dates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Forecast Dates')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.tight_layout()
    plt.show()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['day'] = pd.to_datetime(data['day'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data['forecast'] = pd.to_datetime(data['forecast'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['day'])]
    data = data[pd.notna(data['forecast'])]
    chart = sns.scatterplot(x='normal', y='actual', data=data)
    chart.axhline(y=data['actual'].mean(), color='r', linestyle='--', label='Actual Mean')
    chart.axvline(x=data['normal'].mean(), color='g', linestyle='--', label='Normal Mean')
    plt.title('Is there a correlation between normal temperature and actual temperature?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
